1 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-3-603 of Title 27A, unless
3 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 When developing the guidelines for an Urban Agriculture Cost
5 Share Program, the Oklahoma Conservation Commission shall consider:
6 1. Prioritizing projects in geographic areas where residents
7 have low levels of access to retail outlets selling healthy and
8 affordable food;
9 2. Building on existing urban agriculture projects to continue
10 to grow community engagement;
11 3. Reviewing approved cost-share methods available through
12 USDA-NRCS to promote urban agriculture, improve urban food security,
13 and enhance green spaces in urban areas; and
14 4. Evaluating if other federal, state, or Oklahoma tribal
15 programs can be enhanced by the inclusion of practices in the
16 Commission's Urban Agriculture Cost Share Program.
17 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-3-604 of Title 27A, unless
19 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. The Conservation Commission shall require applicants to
21 submit information, forms and reports as necessary to properly and
22 efficiently administer the Urban Agriculture Cost Share Program.
23 B. Persons may apply to a conservation district for cost share
24 funds for eligible urban agriculture initiatives in the State of
